        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d198fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London,
                        via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpts]<note n="2" xml:id="d198fn2">Other portions
                            of this telegram are printed <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_18">p. 18</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-26">26 November
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 658. Top Secret and Personal from the President for the Prime
                    Minister.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>In regard to paragraph six of your 825,<note n="3" xml:id="d198fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> there should be no difficulty for us in
                    equipping so much of a French occupation force as they may need in a disarmed
                    Germany from the military equipment that we will take from the German Army when
                    it surrenders or is destroyed.</p>
                <p>In any event, I have at the present time no authority under which it would be
                    possible for me to equip any post-war foreign army, and the prospect of getting
                    such authority from the Congress is more than doubtful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
